            <h4>Waves Confined by Reflections</h4>
             <div class="lesson-content-memo">Wave back</div>       
            <strong>Standing Waves</strong> arise when waves are confined within an 
            enclosed container. At each location, the amplitude of the oscillation remains constant over time.
            Only certain patterns are possible - 
            those that arise from <strong>Constructive Interference</strong> of 
            the reflections from the boundaries. <strong>Destructive 
            Interference</strong> eliminates other patterns. This gives rise 
            to certain allowed modes of oscillation (or natural resonances) and is the origin 
            of quantization. 
                <br/><br/>
